commit.message: Add Ruby 3.3 to CI and bump actions/checkout to v4

Minor refactor to Warning.clear

Don't start the begin/ensure handling until the appropriate state
has been captured.  Synchronize the capturing of state.

Fixes #18

Allowing passing a block to Warning.clear

If a block is passed, the values are only cleared within the block and
restored after the block ends.

commit.message:
Tweak exception message added in previous commit

Fixes #17

Disallow Warning.process(Regexp, &block)

Previously, the following code worked by accident:

  Warning.process(/foo/) { :raise }

Calling Warning.process a second time resulted in
  # => ArgumentError (comparison of Regexp with Regexp failed)

This commit checks the type of passed path to be a String.

commit.message:
Use Regexp#match? instead of String#=~ for matching

This should be faster, though speed doesn't matter much here.

Fix invalid use of assert_raises

assert_raises does not accept regexps to match messages.  Test that the
exception message includes the expected text in a separate call.

This avoids the need to have a local variable to record the warning.

Don't test for Fixnum/Bignum warnings on Ruby 3.2

Ruby 3.2 removed these constants.
Add support for :void_context as regexp argument to Warning.ignore

Support :category keyword to Warning.warn on Ruby 3.0

This accepts but ignores a category keyword.  If a category keyword
is passed and non-nil, it includes it when calling super. Otherwise,
it only calls super with the warning string.

Update tests to pass on Ruby 3.0

Mostly switching instance variable warnings to global variable
warnings.

Adjust CI to be CRuby 2.4-3.0

Also adjust CI gemfile.

Fix typo in documentation comment

The document is for `Warning.process`, but `Warning.ignore` is called unexpectedly in the document.
